# COMPILER NOTES FOR THE CPP MODULE

## Linux

Compile Python Module on Linux (Ubuntu) using g++ and pybind11 

Step 1: Install pybind11 with `pip install pybind11`:

Step 2: Run the following line in your terminal:

```
g++ -O3 -Wall -shared -std=c++11 -fPIC `python3 -m pybind11 --includes` *.cpp -o solvermodule`python3-config --extension-suffix`
```

This will create an SO-file containing the compiled module.

## Windows

Compile Python Module on Windows using CMake, Visual Studio 17, and pybind11:

Step 1: Install CMake and Visual Studio 17.

Step 2: Create the following `CMakeLists.txt` file:

```
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.5)
project(solvermodule)

add_subdirectory(pybind11)

file(GLOB SOURCES "*.cpp")

pybind11_add_module(solvermodule ${SOURCES})

set_target_properties(solvermodule PROPERTIES CXX_STANDARD 11)
```

Step 3: From the command prompt, run the following commands:

```
mkdir build

cd build

cmake ..

cmake --build . --config Release
```

This will create a PYD-file containing the compiled module.